# Cloudflare Pages security headers (PRODUCTION, served on every response).
# A generic, strict baseline. Tighten or relax per project.
#
# CSP notes / maintenance:
#   - script-src 'self': Astro inlines small hoisted <script> chunks into the
#     HTML. The build hook `injectCspScriptHashes` (astro.config.mjs) appends a
#     sha256- hash for every executable inline script to the `script-src` line
#     below AT BUILD TIME — so the deployed dist/_headers carries the hashes even
#     though this source file shows only 'self'. Never add 'unsafe-inline' to
#     script-src; the hook keeps it strict automatically as scripts change.
#   - style-src needs 'unsafe-inline' (Astro inlines critical CSS + style="" attrs
#     carrying section padding/alignment tokens; those cannot be hashed).
#   - JSON-LD (<script type="application/ld+json">) is data, not executed: no hash needed.
#   - img-src allows https://cdn.sanity.io so Sanity-hosted images load once the CMS
#     is connected (urlFor() serves them straight from the CDN).
#   - form-action 'self' https://form.taxi: if you post to a third-party form host, add it here
#     (see src/components/ContactForm.astro).
#   - Analytics (privacy-friendly, e.g. Plausible/Fathom/Cloudflare Web Analytics):
#     inject the snippet via BaseLayout's <slot name="head" />, then allow its host
#     here — add the script origin to script-src and the ingest origin to
#     connect-src (e.g. script-src ... https://plausible.io; connect-src 'self' https://form.taxi
#     https://plausible.io). An external script needs its host, not a hash.
#
# NOTE: this file governs PRODUCTION only. The separate preview Worker sets its own
# Content-Security-Policy (frame-ancestors for the Sanity Studio) in src/middleware.ts.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'self'; frame-src https://player.vimeo.com; img-src 'self' data: https://cdn.sanity.io; font-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://form.taxi; form-action 'self' https://form.taxi; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN

# Content-gehashte Build-Assets (/_astro/*) ändern den Dateinamen bei jeder
# Änderung – also dauerhaft cachebar. immutable = Browser fragt nie nach.
/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Selbstgehostete Fonts: stabile Namen, lange cachen (ohne immutable, falls eine
# Schrift mal unter gleichem Namen ausgetauscht wird).
/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000
